The syntax for declaring a simple variable in OpenROAD is:
name = datatype [with null|not null] [not default|with default|[with] default defaultvalue]
For example: i = integer;

To specify a different default value, you must include the default clause in the variable declaration. The
default value must be null, a literal, or one of the system constants defined in the Language Reference Guide.
For example: i = integer not null default false;

To declare a reference variable in OpenROAD, use the following syntax:
name = class [ [with] default null]
For example: strobj = StringObject;

You can check for a null reference variable using the 'is null' operator. For example:
if a is null then
    /* processing statements */
endif;

You can create objects for reference variables using the Create method, defined for the Class class. For example:
a = Addr.Create();    /* Creates an Addr object */
a.Street = 'main street';
a.City = 'dallas';
